<typeStatus box="[1173,1223,974,997]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingRegion box="[824,921,1004,1027]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Arizona</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="222" pageNumber="223" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="222.[694,1224,182,1437]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">
DISCUSSION: The redescription is based on a single 
<typeStatus box="[800,900,1062,1085]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">paratype</typeStatus>
male. Knight (1964) indicated that L. L. Stitt, the collector of the only known specimens of this taxon, had collected the host plant but did not put the name on the insect specimens. Why Knight mentions this issue is not clear to me, because he did not place host labels on the specimens either, nor did he make mention of the identity of the host in his description of the new species.
</paragraph>
